TY  - JOUR
AU  - Levitt, Steven D.
AU  - Venkatesh, Sudhir Alladi
T1  - An Economic Analysis of a Drug-Selling Gang's Finances*
PY  - 2000
Y1  - 2000/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355300554908
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 115
IS  - 3
SP  - 755
EP  - 789
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We use a unique data set detailing the financial activities of a drug-selling street gang to analyze gang economics. On average, earnings in the gang are somewhat above the legitimate labor market alternative. The enormous risks of drug selling, however, more than offset this small wage premium. Compensation within the gang is highly skewed, and the prospect of future riches, not current wages, is the primary economic motivation. The gang engages in repeated gang wars and sometimes prices below marginal cost. Our results suggest that economic factors alone are unlikely to adequately explain individual participation in the gang or gang behavior.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355300554908
ER  - 



